@SarinaKilham From @arcticdatactr's @sjeanetteclark: If your data are audio files of interviews, relevant metadata might include the file name, description, size, and type. A #spreadsheet or #csv is one way to track this information, a #metadata standard (such as #EML or #ISO) is even better.
